channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Optimising Event-Driven Spiking Neural Network with Regularisation and Cutoff
item.description: Two novel optimisation techniques are presented to achieve AOI-SNNs: a regularisation and a cutoff.

item.title: Modeling Non-deterministic Human Behaviors in Discrete Food Choices
item.description: We establish a non-deterministic model that predicts a user's food preferences from their demographic information.

item.title: Maximum Mean Discrepancy Kernels for Predictive and Prognostic Modeling of Whole Slide Images
item.description: How similar are two images?

item.title: On the Expressive Power of Geometric Graph Neural Networks
item.description: The expressive power of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) has been studied extensively through the Weisfeiler-Leman (WL) graph isomorphism test.

item.title: Triplet Contrastive Learning for Unsupervised Vehicle Re-identification
item.description: For the inter-class instance, a hybrid contrastive loss (HCL) re-defines the sample correlations by approaching the positive cluster features and leaving the all negative instance features.

item.title: StyleGAN-T: Unlocking the Power of GANs for Fast Large-Scale Text-to-Image Synthesis
item.description: Text-to-image synthesis has recently seen significant progress thanks to large pretrained language models, large-scale training data, and the introduction of scalable model families such as diffusion and autoregressive models.

item.title: Sensemaking About Contraceptive Methods Across Online Platforms
item.description: Selecting a birth control method is a complex healthcare decision.

item.title: Exploring Active 3D Object Detection from a Generalization Perspective
item.description: To alleviate the high annotation cost in LiDAR-based 3D object detection, active learning is a promising solution that learns to select only a small portion of unlabeled data to annotate, without compromising model performance.

item.title: ddml: Double/debiased machine learning in Stata
item.description: We introduce the package ddml for Double/Debiased Machine Learning (DDML) in Stata.

item.title: StockEmotions: Discover Investor Emotions for Financial Sentiment Analysis and Multivariate Time Series
item.description: There has been growing interest in applying NLP techniques in the financial domain, however, resources are extremely limited.

item.title: Prediction-Powered Inference
item.description: We introduce prediction-powered inference $\unicode{x2013}$ a framework for performing valid statistical inference when an experimental data set is supplemented with predictions from a machine-learning system such as AlphaFold.

item.title: Debiasing the Cloze Task in Sequential Recommendation with Bidirectional Transformers
item.description: The most common approach to mitigating exposure bias in recommendation has been Inverse Propensity Scoring (IPS), which consists of down-weighting the interacted predictions in the loss function in proportion to their propensities of exposure, yielding a theoretically unbiased learning.

item.title: Energy Prediction using Federated Learning
item.description: In this work, we demonstrate the viability of using federated learning to successfully predict energy consumption as well as solar production for all households within a certain network using low-power and low-space consuming embedded devices.

item.title: SPEC5G: A Dataset for 5G Cellular Network Protocol Analysis
item.description: 5G is the 5th generation cellular network protocol.

item.title: Bidirectional Propagation for Cross-Modal 3D Object Detection
item.description: Recent works have revealed the superiority of feature-level fusion for cross-modal 3D object detection, where fine-grained feature propagation from 2D image pixels to 3D LiDAR points has been widely adopted for performance improvement.

item.title: Champion Solution for the WSDM2023 Toloka VQA Challenge
item.description: In this report, we present our champion solution to the WSDM2023 Toloka Visual Question Answering (VQA) Challenge.

item.title: Propagation of Linear Uncertainties through Multiline Thru-Reflect-Line Calibration
item.description: This study proposes a linear approach for propagating uncertainties in the multiline thru-reflect-line (TRL) calibration method for vector network analyzers.

item.title: An Empirical Study of Metrics to Measure Representational Harms in Pre-Trained Language Models
item.description: Large-scale Pre-Trained Language Models (PTLMs) capture knowledge from massive human-written data which contains latent societal biases and toxic contents.

item.title: Unsupervised Data Selection for TTS: Using Arabic Broadcast News as a Case Study
item.description: Several high-resource Text to Speech (TTS) systems currently produce natural, well-established human-like speech.

item.title: Tier Balancing: Towards Dynamic Fairness over Underlying Causal Factors
item.description: The pursuit of long-term fairness involves the interplay between decision-making and the underlying data generating process.

item.title: Adapting a Language Model While Preserving its General Knowledge
item.description: This paper shows that the existing methods are suboptimal and proposes a novel method to perform a more informed adaptation of the knowledge in the LM by (1) soft-masking the attention heads based on their importance to best preserve the general knowledge in the LM and (2) contrasting the representations of the general and the full (both general and domain knowledge) to learn an integrated representation with both general and domain-specific knowledge.

item.title: Improving Deep Regression with Ordinal Entropy
item.description: In computer vision, it is often observed that formulating regression problems as a classification task often yields better performance.

item.title: Poor Man's Quality Estimation: Predicting Reference-Based MT Metrics Without the Reference
item.description: Machine translation quality estimation (QE) predicts human judgements of a translation hypothesis without seeing the reference.

item.title: Exploring Methods for Building Dialects-Mandarin Code-Mixing Corpora: A Case Study in Taiwanese Hokkien
item.description: In natural language processing (NLP), code-mixing (CM) is a challenging task, especially when the mixed languages include dialects.

item.title: Counterfactual Explanation and Instance-Generation using Cycle-Consistent Generative Adversarial Networks
item.description: However, since it is often not straight forward to obtain the labels in many application domains such as in medical image, classification-based approaches have become the de facto standard to perform the diagnosis.

item.title: Recurrent Contour-based Instance Segmentation with Progressive Learning
item.description: In this work, we propose a novel deep network architecture, i. e., PolySnake, for contour-based instance segmentation.

item.title: ExClaim: Explainable Neural Claim Verification Using Rationalization
item.description: We introduce a novel claim verification approach, namely: ExClaim, that attempts to provide an explainable claim verification system with foundational evidence.

item.title: Transforming Unstructured Text into Data with Context Rule Assisted Machine Learning (CRAML)
item.description: We describe a method and new no-code software tools enabling domain experts to build custom structured, labeled datasets from the unstructured text of documents and build niche machine learning text classification models traceable to expert-written rules.

item.title: Is ChatGPT A Good Translator? A Preliminary Study
item.description: This report provides a preliminary evaluation of ChatGPT for machine translation, including translation prompt, multilingual translation, and translation robustness.

item.title: Massively Parallel Genetic Optimization through Asynchronous Propagation of Populations
item.description: We present Propulate, an evolutionary optimization algorithm and software package for global optimization and in particular hyperparameter search.

item.title: Self-Organization Towards $1/f$ Noise in Deep Neural Networks
item.description: Despite $1/f$ noise being ubiquitous in both natural and artificial systems, no general explanations for the phenomenon have received widespread acceptance.

item.title: Self-Supervised Learning for Data Scarcity in a Fatigue Damage Prognostic Problem
item.description: This paper aims to investigate whether pre-training DL models in a self-supervised way on unlabelled sensors data can be useful for RUL estimation with only Few-Shots Learning, i. e. with scarce labelled data.

item.title: Differential Privacy in Cooperative Multiagent Planning
item.description: We synthesize policies that are robust to privacy by reducing the value of the total correlation.

item.title: Visual Semantic Relatedness Dataset for Image Captioning
item.description: Modern image captioning system relies heavily on extracting knowledge from images to capture the concept of a static story.

item.title: Robot Skill Learning Via Classical Robotics-Based Generated Datasets: Advantages, Disadvantages, and Future Improvement
item.description: This article argues that a dataset created using a classical robotics algorithm is a crucial part of future development.

item.title: Source-free Subject Adaptation for EEG-based Visual Recognition
item.description: In this paper, we introduce a novel and practical problem setup, namely source-free subject adaptation, where the source subject data are unavailable and only the pre-trained model parameters are provided for subject adaptation.

item.title: Plan To Predict: Learning an Uncertainty-Foreseeing Model for Model-Based Reinforcement Learning
item.description: In Model-based Reinforcement Learning (MBRL), model learning is critical since an inaccurate model can bias policy learning via generating misleading samples.

item.title: Learning Frequency-Specific Quantization Scaling in VVC for Standard-Compliant Task-driven Image Coding
item.description: This is a well-known method for the human visual system, where scaling lists are derived from psycho-visual models.

item.title: causalgraph: A Python Package for Modeling, Persisting and Visualizing Causal Graphs Embedded in Knowledge Graphs
item.description: This paper describes a novel Python package, named causalgraph, for modeling and saving causal graphs embedded in knowledge graphs.

item.title: Explainable Multilayer Graph Neural Network for Cancer Gene Prediction
item.description: The identification of cancer genes is a critical, yet challenging problem in cancer genomics research.

item.title: Improving Sketch Colorization using Adversarial Segmentation Consistency
item.description: We leverage semantic image segmentation from a general-purpose panoptic segmentation network to generate an additional adversarial loss function.

item.title: Who Should I Engage with At What Time? A Missing Event Aware Temporal Graph Neural Network
item.description: In real-world applications, events are not always observable, and estimating event time is as important as predicting future events.

item.title: Differentially Private Online Bayesian Estimation With Adaptive Truncation
item.description: We propose a novel online and adaptive truncation method for differentially private Bayesian online estimation of a static parameter regarding a population.

item.title: Fast Inference in Denoising Diffusion Models via MMD Finetuning
item.description: Our findings show that the proposed method is able to produce high-quality samples in a fraction of the time required by widely-used diffusion models, and outperforms state-of-the-art techniques for accelerated sampling.

item.title: Enhancing Deep Learning with Scenario-Based Override Rules: a Case Study
item.description: Deep neural networks (DNNs) have become a crucial instrument in the software development toolkit, due to their ability to efficiently solve complex problems.

item.title: FECANet: Boosting Few-Shot Semantic Segmentation with Feature-Enhanced Context-Aware Network
item.description: Few-shot semantic segmentation is the task of learning to locate each pixel of the novel class in the query image with only a few annotated support images.

item.title: Cooperative Distributed MPC via Decentralized Real-Time Optimization: Implementation Results for Robot Formations
item.description: We discuss the implementation via decentralized optimization algorithms.

item.title: CEnt: An Entropy-based Model-agnostic Explainability Framework to Contrast Classifiers' Decisions
item.description: Our Contrastive Entropy-based explanation method, CEnt, approximates a model locally by a decision tree to compute entropy information of different feature splits.

item.title: The role of noise in denoising models for anomaly detection in medical images
item.description: Denoising methods, for instance classical denoising autoencoders (DAEs) and more recently emerging diffusion models, are a promising approach, however naive application of pixelwise noise leads to poor anomaly detection performance.

item.title: Interpreting CNN Predictions using Conditional Generative Adversarial Networks
item.description: Supplying that information has two main challenges: how to represent this information in a form that is feedable to the GANs and how to effectively feed the representation to the GAN.
